The paper deals with the design of linear precoders for the MIMO multiple access channel (MAC) with statistical channel state information (CSI) and finite alphabet inputs. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with the transmission of data over a wireless channel. The paper also considers the practical aspect of finite alphabet inputs, which could fall under the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes an iterative algorithm for determining the precoders, which could fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
